So, how do we make sense of the disproportionate importance of the partnership function to the investment allocated towards partnership resources? Execs are starting to believe in partnerships as a value driver for their businesses, but many donÃ¢Â€Â™t understand the mechanism by which partnerships create value, which makes it hard to get executive sponsorship, and therefore budget, for partnership Most execs still see partnerships as an art - something that requires a special eye, attention to detail, and maybe a hint of luck to create success However, the partnership function is making a shift to a Ã¢Â€Âœscience,Ã¢Â€Â where consistent inputs yield consistent The inputs are best practices from the partner community, applied with tools built to serve the partnership function The outcome is measurable As the shift from art to science gains steam, the number of Ecosystem Management companies in ForresterÃ¢Â€Â™s Channel Software Tech Stack doubled from to , and the investment into partner ecosystem solutions exceeded $1 billion in ( Jay McBain ). These stats are leading indicators that Partnership Teams are becoming successful pitching to the , and maybe even that weÃ¢Â€Â™re starting to see top down directives for Partnership Teams to start automating their ItÃ¢Â€Â™s the decade of partnerships and itÃ¢Â€Â™s time that partnership teams are seen as first class citizens, which means we need a dedicated tech Partner Fleet takes a big step toward that objective by offering a partner marketplace platform that allows companies to launch a world class, whitelabeled marketplace without requiring engineers or marketers to step away from their day jobs to build a custom If youÃ¢Â€Â™d like to see what this new product category is all about, get a demo with our team or request a free trial . If you can wrap your head around that, youÃ¢Â€Â™re beginning to pick up Our Story It all started with a simple idea, an idea born out of the frustrations of seeing what is arguably one of the greatest innovations in human history, being Bitcoin, A Electronic Cash System birthed something that was truly micro and even nanopayments, Payments for fractions of a penny on the internet with practically no cost was set to disrupt However, something The narrative What was once a sparkling new promise of things to come, businesses to be built, and monopolies to be disrupted, suddenly turned into a circus that birthed endless scams, pump and dumps, and a mindset that seems to value speculation over usefulness and actual After standing on the sidelines for six years, two of the founders of Haste decided it was time to do It was time to show a confused mainstream audience the power of Bitcoin as it was originally Joe and Dan, two professional baseball players turned entrepreneurs asked themselves three simple questions: Why are people not getting it? (Bitcoin that is) What s the easiest way to demonstrate a micropayment to a mainstream audience? How can we split a quarter up into tiny pieces and instantly send it to hundreds of people? Haste s HLP gaming concept was After building and showing some success with a simple game called, " Haste ", Joe and Dan went to friends and colleagues, Eric and Keith LaForce, a set of twin brothers, with the idea of taking their simple "tap game" to another Loving the idea, and seeing the vision, Eric and Keith abruptly quit their jobs and joined the team as Technical , hitting the ground running with one goal in mind, deliver the world s first Haste Leaderboard Payout HLP gaming Haste Arcade Pictured above from left to right : Joe De Pinto, Dan Wagner, Eric LaForce, and Keith LaForce Get in touch Mail Text Message +1 (424) Located Los Angeles, CA Send us a message Thank you! Requests for Psychedelics Startups Home About Requests for Startups Contact Podcast Requests for Psychedelics Startups A collection of psychedelic business ideas and research directions that Empath Ventures is especially interested in Psychedelic medicine has the potential to transform the lives of But to fulfill this potential, much work is required and many companies must be This "Request for Psychedelics Startups" is a collection of business ideas and research directions that Empath Ventures is especially interested in Of course, we re open to hearing pitches from any startup in the psychedelics space, even if they aren t working on one of the ideas Beyond Mental Health While most psychedelics startups are focused on treating depression, anxiety and PTSD, we believe that psychedelics have the potential to treat conditions that are not normally considered "mental health" For example, % of the body s serotonin is made in the gut , and altered levels of this peripheral serotonin have been linked to diseases such as irritable bowel syndrome, cardiovascular disease, and Since psychedelics function primarily by agonizing the body s serotonin receptors, could they be used to treat the aforementioned indications? Sexual Dysfunction Enhancement Sexuality is as much mental as it is Some psychedelic compounds like and are well known to increase arousal and Could psychedelics offer relief to those suffering from sexual dysfunctions and disorders ? Another thread here: the line between "treating sexual dysfunction" and "sexual enhancement" is a blurry one (see men that don t actually have erectile dysfunction taking Viagra). Many sexual enhancement products (like poppers) are of questionable Could psychedelics offer a safer alternative to current "sexual enhancement" drugs? Digital Addiction Internet addiction disorder is a growing problem in the There are anecdotal reports of psychedelics helping break video game addiction, and the science shows that receptor agonists hold promise in treating addictive tendencies . Side Note: Empath Ventures is very interested in any technology that helps us control our digital devices rather than our digital devices controlling Please reach out if you re working on any solution to this Digital Therapeutics Can we achieve psychedelic states without psychedelic drugs? Virtual reality and other digital technologies might allow those who cannot take psychedelic drugs due to health, social or personal reasons to reap the therapeutic benefits of the psychedelic Sex and Gender Specific Psychedelic Therapies Sex and gender differences in mental disorders are among the most stable findings in psychiatry and there is evidence that men and women synthesize serotonin at different rates . It makes sense then that every part of the psychedelic therapy process - the drug, the dosing, and the therapy itself - might be adjusted based on the patient s biological Ethical, Sustainable and Economical Psychedelics Supply Chains Increased demand for psychedelic drugs will put pressure on natural sources of psychedelics like the Sonoran Desert Toad , Peyote Cactus and Ayahausca Vine . Synthetic alternatives can be expensive and the chemical extraction process can have negative environmental impacts . We re interested in startups working to create an ethical, sustainable, and economical psychedelic supply Psychedelics for Longevity and There are several pathways through which psychedelics might impact aging, longevity, lifespan and For one, psychedelics are known to have powerful effects, and inflammation seems to be associated with aging . More generally, serotonin is known to regulate biological and behavioral aging in animal This seems like a promising direction for Integrating Psychedelics with Mainstream Medicine In the future, "psychedelic medicine" will be simply known as "medicine". To realize this future, we need technologies and services that enable existing healthcare workers to provide psychedelic This could be anything from training programs, to referral networks, to shared spaces for therapy We re interested in anything that makes it easier for doctors to begin offering psychedelic medicine to their Applications of Crypto and Distributed Ledger Technology to Psychedelic Research It can be difficult to get funding for basic scientific Crypto projects like Molecule and VitaDao are creating new models for funding speculative drug research and We also think crypto mechanisms may play a role in enabling large scale, decentralized, clinical trials, in which participants are compensated for their efforts and anonymity is preserved in a way that is not easy with Web2 We are interested in any legitimate application of DLT to funding and scaling psychedelic research - no "shroomcoin" meme BS Beyond Psychedelics The psychedelic drugs receiving the most attention at the moment (psilocybin, LSD, MDMA, DMT) are all But there are other hallucinogenic drugs that don t agonize the receptor - and some that do
